import pyautogui
import time

try:
    # Press Win key to open Start menu
    pyautogui.press('win')
    time.sleep(1)

    # Type "Clock" to search
    pyautogui.write('Clock', interval=0.1)
    time.sleep(1)

    # Press Enter to launch the first result
    pyautogui.press('enter')
    time.sleep(2)

    # Verify window appeared by checking for unique title substring
    import pygetwindow as gw
    titles = [w.title for w in gw.getAllWindows() if w.title and 'clock' in w.title.lower()]
    if not titles:
        raise Exception("Clock window not detected after launch")

    print("EXECUTION_SUCCESS")
except Exception as e:
    print("FAILED:", str(e))
